dspace-development.title: [dataspace] Ensure that submissions from sak2 properly populate the Task Pool for Research Data Management

comments.body:
I am currently failing to find the affected Item, as the metadata does not even appear to be in the database for the title:

```bash
dataspace_prod_db=# select resource_id from metadatavalue where text_value like '%BLACK PROF%';
 resource_id
-------------
(0 rows)
dataspace_prod_db=# select resource_id from metadatavalue where text_value like '%black professionals%';
 resource_id
-------------
        1306
        1306
(2 rows)
```

While trying to understand why this Item is missing, I have found that the IP address of the PostgreSQL database host cannot be located from within the GCP dashboard. Further, I also cannot access this by SSH, however, it is currently being used for active DataSpace deployments:

https://github.com/PrincetonUniversityLibrary/princeton-5/blob/dataspace-prod/prod.properties#L59

The following Items have been submitted by the user account `steven.knowlton`:

```bash
"Reimagining public safety in Newark", "Miami-Dade County Public Schools: The hidden truth", "Police in schools are not the answer to school shootings", "Democracy rising: The end of Florida‚Äôs history of felony disenfranchisement and launch of a new age of empowerment", "The genius of ordinary people: How the Ferguson Collaborative became the voice of the community", "The carceral state of Arizona: The human cost of being confined", "Our voices, our votes: Felony disenfranchisement and reentry in Mississippi", "Antiracism toolkit for allies in scholarly publishing", "Antiracism toolkit for organizations in scholarly publishing", "Antiracism toolkit for Black, Indigenous, and People of Color in scholarly publishing", "Over-policing, under-policing, or both? An analysis of police resource allocation", "Are U.S. cities underpoliced?: Theory and evidence", "More COPS, less crime", "Race, ethnicity, and the criminal justice system", "Mr. ZIP", "Postal saving system", "The postal service‚Äôs role in civil defense during the Cold War", "Telegraph: Early postal role", "V-Mail", "Steamboats", "Mail by rail", "Star routes", "Overland mail to California in the 1850s", "Airmail: A brief history", "The pneumatic mail tubes: New York's hidden highway and its development", "Electric vehicles in the Postal Service", "Refunding our communities: A pathway forward to real public safety", "Election protection report: Issues New Jersey voters encountered from October 15 through November 3, 2020"
```

Please note that none of these match the title `MEMORIES OF PUBLIC LIBRARIES IN ORAL HISTORIES OF ACCOMPLISHED BLACK PROFESSIONALS`

The user `sak2` currently has 769 Items submitted by their user account:

```bash
jruby-9.2.13.0 :050 > items2.length
 => 769
jruby-9.2.13.0 :051 > items2.last.submitter.getEmail
 => "sak2"
```

There do not appear to be any title-based matches for these Item submissions either:

```bash
ruby-9.2.13.0 :056 > puts titles2.select { |t| t.downcase.include?("public") }
Whose Heritage?:  Public Symbols of the Confederacy
Policing in America: Understanding Public Attitudes Toward the Police: Results from a National Survey
Black Lives Matter: The Schott 50 State Report on Public Education and Black Males
Given Half a Chance: The Schott 50 State Report on Public Education and Black Males
The Urgency of Now: The Schott 50 State Report on Public Education and Black Males
A New Diverse Majority: Students of Color in the South‚Äôs Public Schools
A New Majority: Low Income Students in the South‚Äôs Public Schools
Achieving a fair and effective COVID-19 response: An open letter to Vice-President Mike Pence, and other federal, state and local leaders from Public Health and Legal Experts in the United States
Newark Public Schools: Budget impacts of underfunding and rapid charter growth
Shortchanging New Jersey students: How inadequate funding has led to reduced staff and growing disparities in the state‚Äôs public schools
Handcuffs on success: The extreme school discipline crisis in Mississippi public schools
Restoring justice in Buffalo public schools: Safe and supportive quality education for all
Restorative justice now! A community review of Alexandria City Public Schools‚Äô implementation of restorative justice
History, the past, and public culture: Results from a national survey
21 pillars for redefining public safety and restoring community trust
```

The following Collections do not grant Research Management Specialists authorization to review submissions:

- https://dataspace.princeton.edu/handle/88435/dsp016q182k16g
- https://dataspace.princeton.edu/handle/88435/dsp01bg257f09p

https://dataspace.princeton.edu/handle/88435/dsp01zw12z7787 was identified as the affected Collection. The Group `ResearchDataReviewer` needed to be authorized for reviewing and approving submissions.
It should also be noted that the ID for the Item which was unavailable is `174339`.

I can confirm that there was only one `WorkflowItem` for this Collection:

```bash
jruby-9.2.13.0 :048 > workflows = org.dspace.workflow.WorkflowItem.findByCollection(DSpace.context, coll1)
 => org.dspace.workflow.WorkflowItem[org.dspace.workflow.WorkflowItem@38aafb53]@716e431d
jruby-9.2.13.0 :049 > workflows.to_a.length
 => 1
```

[![Coverage Status](https://coveralls.io/builds/62536720/badge)](https://coveralls.io/builds/62536720)

coverage: 95.341% (-0.07%) from 95.409% when pulling **2bbe5710287e3b334d26a124ce61aa0b90e6bc17 on 3705-upgrade-vite** into **be8b0402db69c44557d893eab7323fcffbfe0b8a on main**.

This is partly a data issue (notice that the name in the 700 field is just some spaces and punctuation): https://catalog.princeton.edu/catalog/99126151302606421/staff_view

However, it does seem that the blacklight-marc gem should be made more resilient against issues like these.  So this bug could be fixed by:

- [ ] Creating a test that recreates this issue in [this file](https://github.com/projectblacklight/blacklight-marc/blob/8cb8050327b079304b81e9531a4a738efc3fe1e6/spec/models/concerns/blacklight/marc/document_export_spec.rb)
- [ ] Writing the code to fix that test
- [ ] Opening a PR to blacklight-marc gem
- [ ] Once that PR is merged and released, upgrading our version of blacklight-marc to one that includes the fix.
